args:
Lily and Victor hurry back to the village they
once saved after learning it has been occupied
by the empire, but are unable to reach it now
that the ice has melted. Victor proposes a
plan to reach it anew, this time by air.
Victor and Lily set off on a journey to deliver\nDragonyule presents, defeating any soldier or\nfiend who stood in their way.
At first, their mission appeared to be\ngoing swimmingly, but then...
Breathe between bites, Lily.\nYour food isn't going anywhere.
So, yeah, you might wanna give that\nplace a wide berth for a while.
How did the empire even get over\nthere? The only path to the village\nis straight across a lake.
People're saying they managed\nto freeze it somehow.
Never mind how I look. I just want\nto know more about what you were\ndiscussing.
Well, it sounds like the empire attacked\nthat village beyond the lake.
All this time, they haven't been able to\ntouch it because it's stuck between the\nwater and some mountains.
But it sounds like they froze the lake and\nwalked right across it. Crazy, right?
I see. Thank you for sharing.
Huh? Hang on! Where are you going?!
That wasn't his kid, was it?\n*gasp* Was he a kidnapper?!
Nah. She was attached to him at the hip.
Weirdest pair of Saint Starfalls\nI've ever seen.
Victor, wait! Why are we going back the\nway we came?
(I really hope I'm wrong.\nBut if I'm not...)
Why are there so many soldiers?
How did they manage that?\nWait. Don't tell me they—
Exactly. They crossed the ice you created.
Then this is all my fault. Oh no...
We don't have the luxury of moping\naround. We need to save them.
But how? They're on guard now,\nand the ice is starting to melt.
If we can't go by land,\nwe go by air.
*pant* I'm so tired after climbing that\nmountain.
But there's someone guarding\nthis entrance to the village, too!\nHow are we gonna get in there?
I already told you. We go by air.
Wait... You mean we're\nJUMPING off here?!
But we'll just go squish and die!
Not with a parachute, we won't.
You'll see soon enough. We're going to\nland in the middle of the village and\ncatch them off guard.
We don't have time to hash this out,\nthough. We need to act now.
On my count—\nfive, four, three, two, one...
Save the sigh of relief for once\nthe mission is over!
Who are you two?! And...why are\nyou dressed like Saint Starfall?

You must be a couple of real party animals
if you've decided to throw a shindig even
with a buncha guys like us around! So,
where's it goin' down? Is there a buffet?!

Sorry. I think I've been workin' too hard
lately. Every time a holiday comes
around, we're gettin' ordered to attack
the Halidom. It's like clockwork.
Then why don't you take\nthe rest of Dragonyule off?
Rest well. Now, Lily, I believe\nwe have some trash to take out.
Now we just have to carry them to the\nother shore on our sleigh and we're done.
You came to save us again!
Victor's the one you should be thanking.
But I couldn't have done anything without\nyou. I would've just given up.
We only saved this village because\nyou were here leading the charge!
Poppycock. A bloodsoaked warrior like\nme has no place ＂saving＂ Dragonyule.
That's not true at all!\nYou make a GREAT Saint Starfall!
Heh. I appreciate the sentiment,\nbut I don't agree. Now, let's go.
Our work is far from done.\nThere are more towns to save.
Keep up the good work, Saint Starfall!
This time, the lakeside village was truly saved.

But word of Victor and Lily's exploits quickly
spread throughout the imperial army, who 
responded in kind with even more ferocious
attacks elsewhere.
So YOU'RE the pain-in-the-neck Saint\nStarfalls we've heard so much about!
Everyone in the empire knows of your\ndark deeds, you red-letter reprobates!
You won't get away from us!
Our run-ins with the empire are getting\nrougher by the day...
Sorry. I'm just getting kinda tired.
Understandable. We've seen\nfirsthand how exhaustion can lead\npeople to do strange things.
We need to bring this to a swift end—\nand I have just the plan.
Ooh! Whatever it is, I'm in all the way.\nWe've gotta protect Dragonyule!
That's the spirit. Now, I hereby\nannounce our next operation.
(That name's so weird! Maybe Victor's\nthe one who needs a little beauty rest.)
But Lily was too tired to argue,\nand decided to go along with it.
Thus was Operation 'Chuting Stars put into\naction...but what, exactly, would it entail?
You'll just have to wait and see!
